<SLUG> BC-SOC-GALAXY-LADN-(SLANG) </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
GALAXY TO PLAY VS. KANSAS CITY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By FRED J. ROBLEDO  
 c.2000 San Gabriel Valley Tribune  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The weight of the MLS semifinal series will fall on the
shoulders of Galaxy strikers Luis Hernandez and Cobi Jones.
</P>
<P>
   The top-seeded Kansas City Wizards posted the stingiest
defensive numbers in league history, led by team USA's 1994 World
Cup starting goalkeeper, Tony Meola. He recorded 15 shutouts en
route to a record-setting 0.92 goals-against average.
</P>
<P>
   The Wizards allowed only 29 goals in 32 regular-season games to
wrestle the Western Division title away from the Galaxy. However,
the Galaxy burned K.C. the last time these teams met at Arrowhead
Stadium, winning 5-1 behind the creativity of Jones, Hernandez and
midfielder Mauricio Cienfuegos in August.
</P>
<P>
   Most teams man-mark either Jones or Hernandez, but Meola said
the Wizards will stick with their zone defense tonight in game one
of the best-of-three series at Arrowhead Stadium.
</P>
<P>
   ``We haven't man-to-manned anybody,'' said Meola. ``We play a
zone defense and are very into trying to cut out the source. If we
don't cut the source out, that's where you get into trouble.
</P>
<P>
   ``These two (Jones and Hernandez) have been man-marked their
whole careers and know how to get open when man-marked. More often
than not, their attack comes from Cienfuegos. We have to limit him.
The more opportunities he provides, the worse off we'll be.''
</P>
<P>
   The back three of K.C.'s defense _ Peter Vermes, Nick Garcia and
Brandon Prideaux _ get most of the credit, but Meola said the
defensive chemistry starts in the midfield.
</P>
<P>
   ``Where we don't get enough credit is with Matt McKeon and Kerry
Zavagnin in the midfield,'' said Meola. ``For me, Kerry has had the
most consistent year on our team. These guys really break plays up
in the midfield.''
</P>
<P>
   Jones and Hernandez played their best game as a strike tandem in
last week's series clinching 5-2 victory over Tampa Bay in the
first round. Hernandez scored a goal and notched three assists.
Jones also had a goal.
</P>
<P>
   ``It takes time to get to know a player,'' Jones said of his
relationship with Hernandez. ``We've missed playing together
because of some qualifiers. Now, we've had some time where we've
been in Los Angeles together. Little by little, everything is
starting to click. It's starting to work. I think we are starting
to complement each other well.''
</P>
<P>
   This is not the shaky Mutiny defense the Galaxy burned in the
playoff opener, however. Jones realizes chances will not come
easily.
</P>
<P>
   ``It will be difficult; this is the toughest team to break
down,'' said Jones.
</P>
<P>
   The Galaxy is 1-1-2 against the Wizards, with each club winning
at home.
</P>
<P>
   ``As long as Kansas City has a good defense and we have a good
offense, it will be an intriguing battle,'' Jones said. ``This is a
playoff matchup that everyone wants.''
</P>
</TEXT>
