   FASHION-NEW YORK _ A. Scott Walton wraps up New York fashion
week by pointing out the biggest trends in spring/summer
womenswear.WITH PHOTOS. (Walton, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   ENTERTAINEMTN/ARTS
</P>
<P>
   COUNTRY-MUSIC _ When country music stars used to dress up, they
wore rhinestone jacks and lacey gowns (often made on a Singer
sewing machine). On Wednesday, the artists who walk onto the stage
of the 34th Country Music Association Awards show are anything but
homemade. Professional stylists have become as important in
Nashville as record producers, creating polished looks for acts
that often have only shopped at Wal-Mart. We talk to the city's
most powerful hairdressers and clothing buyers _ Melanie Shelley
(who creates those crazy hairdos for the Dixie Chicks), Trish
Townsend (nominee Lee Ann Womack and host Vince Gill), and Jamie
Kimmle (Jo Dee Messina). A look inside the fashion factory that is
now Nashville. (The Altanta Journal-Constitution) FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   WEST-WING _ WASHINGTON _ How is the NBC-TV series ``The West
Wing'' viewed by denizens of the REAL West Wing? (Deans, Cox News
Service) WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   Moving in (w) Washington and (e) entertainment categories.
</P>
<P>
   WAN: Atlanta, Entertainment/Arts, Television FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   WESTWING _ Even a computer might have trouble calculating the
likelihood of three unrelated actors from a city the size of
Dayton, Ohio, starring together on a hit, Emmy-winning network
television program. Dayton Daily News columnist D.L. Stewart makes
a visit to the set of ``The West Wing,'' where Martin Sheen, Rob
Lowe and Allison Janney all have Miami Valley roots. He tells all _
except how last season's cliffhanger is resolved. (Dayton Daily
News) FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   SPIVEY-HALL _ Spivey Hall, one of the area's most acoustically
perfect concert venues, celebrates its 10th anniversary this year.
A look back at where it came from, where it's been and where it's
going. (Ruhe, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution) FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   PLAYWRIGHT _ A conversation with Pulitzer Prize-winning
playwright Donald Margulies, whose ``Dinner With Friends'' is in
the midst of a monthlong run at the Alliance Theatre. He talks
about what it's like to win the Pulitzer, where DWF came from,
adapting Tom Wolfe's Atlanta-set ``A Man in Full'' for NBC,
playwrighting, middle age and much more. (Janich, The Altanta
Journal-Constitution) FOR SUNDAY
</P>
<P>
   E-ARTS _ News about the arts on the Internet. (Staff, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) FOR SUNDAY
</P>
