Alonzo Mourning of the U.S. battles Lithuania's Eurelijus Zukauskas
during their Olympic semifinal match, Friday. In a game that wasn't
decided until the final shot missed by about a foot, the United
States edged Lithuania 85-83 Friday night to reach the gold medal
game. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY14) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-RUN-WOMEN-6
-- Heike Drechsler of Germany after winning the gold medal Friday
in the women's long jump competition of the 2000 Summer Olympics.
Drechsler ended Marion Jones's bid for five gold medals in Sydney
by securing her second long jump title on day 14 of the Olympic
Games. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY13) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-RUN-WOMEN-5
-- Marion Jones of the United States grimmaces after fouling on her
final jump Friday in the women's long jump of the 2000 Summer
Olympic Games. Heike Drechsler of Germany ended Jones's bid for
five gold medals in Sydney by securing her second long jump title
on day 14 of the Olympic Games. Jones won the bronze. (Barton
Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
