OLY--CANOE-KAYAK-ARATON -- Israeli kayaker Michael Kolganov cuts
through the water during the men's K1 semifinal races in Penrith
Lake, west of Sydney, Friday. Kolganov finished third and qualified
for the finals. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY10) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-SOC-VECSEY --
Mia Hamm looks at her silver medal as her somber teammates,
Michelle French, left, and Shannon MacMillan st0od for the medal
ceremony, Thursday. The Dream Team never lost, and probably never
will, but the U.S. soccer team did lose to their worthy opponent
from Norway, which only adds to their luster as the greatest
American women's team - ever. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY9) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-BKO-MEN-3-- An
Australian basketball team fan wears with the number of player
Andrew Gaze watches as his team loses to France, Friday in the
Olympic semifinal match. France crushed Australia 76-52 to reach
the Olympic men's basketball finals for the first time since 1948.
(Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
