crushed Australia 76-52 to reach the Olympic men's basketball
finals for the first time since 1948. (Chang W. Lee/The New York
Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY5) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-BKO-WOMEN-3--
Yolanda Griffith of the U.S. basketball team, on the floor, fights
for control of the ball against South Korea's Jung-Ok Yang in their
Olympic semifinal match, Friday. The Americans defeated South Korea
78-65 to advance to the finals against Australia. (Chang W. Lee/The
New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY4) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-BKO-WOMEN-2--
Yolanda Griffith of the U.S. basketball team takes a shot over
South Korea's Sun-Min Jung in their semifinal match, Friday at the
2000 Summer Olympic Games. The Americans defeated South Korea 78-65
to advance to the finals against Australia. (Chang W. Lee/The New
York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY3) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-BKO-WOMEN-1--
Nell Ann Fortner, right, coach of the U.S. women's basketball team,
with players Sheryl Swoopes, center, and Yolanda Griffith after the
Americans defeated South Korea 78-65 on Friday to advance to the
finals against Australia. (Chang W. Lee/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY2) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-RUN-WOMEN-2--
Heike Drechsler, the 35-year-old German great who ended Marion
Jones' quest to be the first track athlete in 76 years, and second
ever, to win five gold medals in the Olympics, in her gold-winning
long jump Friday. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (OLY1) SYDNEY, Australia -- Sept. 29, 2000 -- OLY-RUN-WOMEN-1--
For the first time in her first Olympics, Jones wasn't looking down
at everyone from the top of the medal stand on Friday. She was
looking up at Heike Drechsler, the 35-year-old German great who
ended Jones' quest to be the first track athlete in 76 years, and
second ever, to win five gold medals in the Olympics. Jones blew
away the competition in the 100 and 200 meters in Sydney. The long
jump, everyone knew, was the weak link in this golden chain. Jones
in the long jump Friday. (Barton Silverman/The New York Times)
</P>
