<P>
   ISRAEL-UNREST (Jerusalem) _ Five Palestinians were killed and at
least 96 injured when violence erupted at the Temple Mount Friday
just as Muslim noon prayers ended. The bloody scene occurred when
Israeli police fired rubber bullets in attempts to disperse
Palestinian youths. Jerusalem's police chief as well as the chief
of border police were injured. And just hours before Rosh Hashana
was to begin, police officers ordered all Jews away from the
Western Wall. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-ELECTIONS (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ Developments following
the Yugoslav elections: the opposition is encouraging nation-wide
acts of civil disobedience to force President Slobodan Milosevic to
step down and accept their victory in the elections. By Steven
Erlanger.
</P>
<P>
   DENMARK-EURO-ASSESS (Copenhagen, Denmark) _ News Analysis: With
the Danish rejection of Europe's common currency, the euro, and the
apparent crumbling of Slobodan Milosevic's government in
Yugoslavia, the vision of what is known as a ``wide'' Europe seems
to have taken the upper hand over the ``deep'' Europe dear to many
German and Gallic hearts. By Roger Cohen.
