contract from the U.S. Army in Redstone Arsenal, Ala., for enhanced
air transportability kits.
</P>
<P>
   Boeing Defense and Space System of Philadelphia won a $559,218
contract from the U.S. Army in Redstone Arsenal, Ala., for engine
air particle separators.
</P>
<P>
   Triumph Controls Inc. of North Wales won a $677,810 contract
from the Defense General Supply Center in Richmond, Va., for
aircraft components and accessories.
</P>
