   HELEN-THOMAS (Washington _ Poor Mr. Lincoln. So many visitors
sleeping in his seven-foot bed. It's fine and proper to have
overnight guests in the lonely White House, but there is a strong
perception that some of the Clintons' invitations have been issued
for a price. By HELEN THOMAS.
