<P>
   ONE BAD COP
</P>
<P>
   LAPD-SCANDAL-CENTERPIECE _ When Rafael Perez was arrested, it
led to the biggest scandal in the history of the Los Angeles Police
Department. Perez did what Rodney King couldn't do: bring the LA
force under federal supervision. By Lou Cannon. 3,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   (Lou Cannon is the author of ``President Reagan: The Role of a
Lifetime'' and ``Official Negligence,'' an account of the Rodney
King trial and the 1992 riots.)
</P>
<P>
   TIPPER'S DANCE
</P>
<P>
   TIPPER-GORE-CENTERPIECE _ For Tipper Gore, it has long been
about keeping her balance, be it her interests, her family or her
mood. She gave up her own pursuits and some of her feminist ideals
for the life of a politician's wife. A look at the many facets of
the candidate's most trusted advisor. By Melinda Henneberger. 1,900
words.
</P>
<P>
   (Melinda Henneberger is a reporter in the Washington bureau of
The New York Times.)
</P>
