A6760 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r e bc-REVIEW-LIFE-TV     09-29 0390
</HEADER>
<BODY>
bc-REVIEW-LIFE-TV
cc,78p3  
<TEXT>
<P>
   &QL; 
The show's better than the title &QL; 
By David Kronke &QL; 
What TV show, save for maybe the ultra-contrived reality series
``Big Brother,'' couldn't use ``That's Life'' for a title?
Fortunately, there's more creativity at work in the show itself
than in its moniker.
</P>
<P>
   Heather Paige Kent stars as Lydia, a 32-year-old Jersey girl who
suddenly discovers what a lout her boyfriend is when he resists her
efforts to enlist in college. She's the all-around sort of guardian
angel who takes care of both the drunks in the bar where she works
and the neighborhood's stray cats.
</P>
<P>
   Lydia's ex isn't the only one with doubts her parents (Paul
Sorvino and Ellen Burstyn) and pals (Debi Mazar and Kristin Bauer)
have their doubts, as well, even though it's eminently clear that
street-smart Lydia is the glue holding this little community
together. Her first day at school is fraught with cutesy mishaps,
from an epic bad-hair day to sputtering car troubles. And oops! the
drunk she cuts off in her bar just happens to be her psych prof.
But nothing keeps our Lydia from giving lip to any highfalutin
diploma-waver this school can toss at her.
</P>
<P>
   CBS compares ``That's Life'' to ``Working Girl'' and ``Educating
Rita,'' but what it most resembles but don't tell anybody is
``Costello,'' Fox's short-lived sitcom from a few years back about
another mouthy dame who dumps her squeeze for a life of the mind.
Fortunately, this incarnation is exponentially less shrill than its
predecessor.
</P>
<P>
   Tonight's premiere episode is crammed with so many quirky
touches and characters that at times you feel exhausted on the show
producers' behalf. It's clearly a case of trying too hard, a
condition that no doubt will be resolved in due time. But at least
they're putting forth the effort.
</P>
<P>
   In the meantime, Kent's an appealing performer, fully capable of
carrying this show until the ensemble cast gels and actually begins
to look like everyone really has known one another for years.
</P>
<P>
   ---``THAT'S LIFE'' &QL; 
What: Dramedy about a Jersey girl all grown up and attending
college in her 30s. &QL; 
The stars: Heather Paige Kent, Ellen Burstyn, Kristin Bauer, Peter
Firth, Kevin Dillon, Paul Sorvino, Debi Mazar. &QL; 
When: 8 tonight; thereafter, 8 p.m. Saturdays. &QL; 
Where: CBS (Channel 2). &QL; 
Our rating: 2 1/2 stars &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-29-00 1530EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
