<P>
   ISRAEL-UNREST (Jerusalem) _ Complete mayhem erupted in the
sacred, contested center of Jerusalem's Old City Friday as stones
and bullets interrupted a day of prayer for Muslims and Jews. Four
Palestinians were killed on the Temple Mount, known in Arabic as
Haram al-Sharif, when hundreds of Israeli officers stormed the
Muslim compound where they rarely set foot. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   With photos NYT1,2,3,4.
</P>
<P>
   DENMARK-EURO-ASSESS (Copenhagen, Denmark) _ News Analysis: There
have long been two competing visions of Europe's future. The first
envisages a loose association of democratic nations; the second
dreams of a federal United States of Europe. With the Danish
rejection of Europe's common currency, the euro, and the apparent
crumbling of Slobodan Milosevic's regime in Yugoslavia, it is the
former vision of what is known as a ``wide'' Europe that seems to
have taken the upper hand over the ``deep'' Europe dear to many
German and Gallic hearts. By Roger Cohen.
</P>
<P>
   YUGO-ELECTIONS (Belgrade, Yugoslavia) _ Darkening movie houses,
blocking roads and shutting shops, tens of thousands of Yugoslavs
heeded opposition calls Friday for nationwide strikes aimed at
forcing President Slobodan Milosevic to accept election defeat and
step down. (Summary from wires.) By Steven Erlanger.
