<HEADLINE>
WHAT'S NOT TO LOVE?
</HEADLINE>
bc-TV-RAYMOND-REVIEW (For use by New York Times News Service clients) 
(Eds: Fact box below. ``Tonight' refers to Mon., Oct. 2) 
Our rating: 3 stars 
 
By DAVID KRONKE 
c. 2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
 
 
No one would begrudge the cast of ``Everybody Loves Raymond'' a
little fun on the company money, so it's nice to see everyone
living it up in Rome. Tonight's fifth-season premiere is, however,
in keeping with the nature of these kinds of ``very special''
episodes: In order to make room for some very pretty scenic vistas,
it's not quite up to the series' usual laugh quotient.
<TEXT>
<P>
   Thanks to Ray's mom Marie's (Doris Roberts) savings, the whole
clan troops to Italy, where the family dynamic runs in ways you'd
expect. Marie orders her troops around on tourist runs; Frank
(Peter Boyle) grumbles amusingly; Debra (Emmy winner Patricia
Heaton) enjoys the exotic culture, while Ray (Ray Romano) is a
sad-sack grouse, particularly when it comes to Europe's vexing lack
of stand-up showers.
</P>
<P>
   Eternally mopey Robert (Brad Garrett), however, falls for a
pretty local, much to her father's and his mother's consternation.
``I've never seen him so happy,'' Marie marvels, ominously adding,
``I don't like it.'' &QL; 
---``EVERYBODY LOVES RAYMOND'' &QL; 
What: Hourlong season premiere of the sitcom, finding Ray, et al.,
in Italy. &QL; 
The stars: Ray Romano, Patricia Heaton, Doris Roberts, Peter Boyle,
Brad Garrett.  &QL; 
Where: CBS (Channel 2). &QL; 
When: 9 tonight. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-29-00 1739EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
